“What is literacy and what does it mean to call computer programming a literacy?”

Literacy is the ability to read and write, and subsequently understand the contents of what you have read in it’s current form and translated into your own language. Literacy in the terms of writing is the ability to follow the rules of the given language, and appropriately construct a written piece following the these rules, and executing grammar, spelling and structure.  

Literacy in computer programming the ability to read and write code in an effective manner. Most computing languages are written in the English language and the coding structure follows western idiosyncrasy such as writing left to write, left hand screen alignment, grammar, syntax and logic processes. Debugging is the ability to read and construct 
